* Implement proper handling of CRLF line endings
* Evaluate memory allocations (we should only allocation on startup unless there is an exceptionally good reason for runtime allocation)
* UTF-8 support with new c unit (c for character)
* Buffered mode (--buffered) where whole file is buffered in memory (should be faster if lots of operations are done back and forth)
* Evalutate need for indexing line endings in pre-pass (perhaps for use in buffered mode)
